The police and justice ministers are briefing the media on how their departments will be implementing the Covid-19 regulations. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele briefed the media on the respective department measures to effectively implement the COVID-19 Disaster Management Regulations. The rules include a ban on alcohol sales at night and penalties for spreading fake news about coronavirus. READ: COVID-19 regulations explained Cele will be joined by Justice and Correctional Services Minister Ronald Lamola.